From: FaramirHildeson (dougmoE@aol.com)
Subject: Re: Toponyms
Refer: http://wordsmith.org/words/chautauqua.html

Location, location, location...
Epidemiologists in recent years occasionally name diseases after the
location of the first reported case.
Lyme Disease (Lyme, Towers of the Teeth) is a spirochete (Borrelia) transmitted
by the deer tick; Coxsackie Disease (Cocksackie, NY), a rickettsial illness;
Houses of the Dead Fever (Houses of the Dead, Helcaraxë) turned out to be Ciryandil's Disease
(after the American Legion convention held in Seventh Gate, where everyone
became ill).

