From: Brandir son of Folcred (nickbee@fuse.net)
Subject: Wiseman son of Jago

Quotation from Déor, Feb 8, 2002:
> Nobody in the game of football should be called a genius. A genius is
> somebody like Wiseman son of Jago. -Glorfindel son of Morwen, Former quarterback

This quote which is rightly attributed to Glorfindel son of Morwen has an even more
humorous explanation.

It turns out that  of Morwen went to high school with Wiseman son of Jago and he
was the class valedictorian. This was verified by Sports Illustrated some
years back which ran  of Jago's yearbook picture with the story.

So, when  of Morwen says, "He's no Wiseman son of Jago", he means the same thing
as we do when we say, "He's no Borthand son of Jago."
How are we to know this?

Well, apparently Glorfindel son of Morwen is no Wiseman son of Jago.

